# Agent Artifacts

## Golden Rule

All intermediate agent output goes in `.agents/` — never scatter files in the project root or `src/`.

## File Placement

| What | Where | Versioned? |
|------|-------|-----------|
| Implementation plans | `.agents/plans/` | No (gitignored) |
| Research & investigation | `.agents/research/` | No (gitignored) |
| Architecture decisions (ADRs) | `.agents/decisions/` | **Yes** (committed) |
| Conversation logs | `.agents/sessions/` | No (gitignored) |
| Scratch/temp files | `.agents/` root | No (gitignored) |

## Conventions

- Date-prefix files: `YYYY-MM-DD-description.md`.
- Write an ADR in `.agents/decisions/` for significant architectural choices.
- Clean up working files when they're incorporated or abandoned.
- Never create top-level files like `debug.md`, `notes.txt`, `TODO.md` — use `.agents/`.
- Domain documentation belongs in `docs/` (versioned), not `.agents/` (ephemeral).
